l-halal","tag-imam-ahmad-ibn-hanbal","tag-ramadan","tag-trade-al-tijarah"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-7aw","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":28698,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/05\/children-fasting-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":27560,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: Children fasting Ramadan if they are able","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 5, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Rabia\u2019 bint Mu\u2019awwidh reported: We would order our children to fast and we would make toys for them out of wool. If one of them cried for food, we would give them those toys until it was time to break fast. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1859, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1136 Grade:\u00a0Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37514,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/12\/15\/halal-tombstone\/","url_meta":{"origin":27560,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Graves: Permission to set up a humble tombstone","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 15, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Mutallib reported: When Uthman ibn Madh\u2019un died, he was brought out for his funeral and he was buried. The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, ordered a man to bring a rock but he was unable to carry it. The Prophet went to it and rolled up his sleeves,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33366,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/09\/07\/fasting-9th-10th-muharram\/","url_meta":{"origin":27560,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on &#8216;Ashura: Fasting 9th and 10th of Muharram","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 7, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, ordered fasting on the day of 'Ashura, the tenth of al-Muharram. Imam al-Tirmidhi said, \u201cIt is reported from Ibn Abbas that he said to fast on the ninth and tenth of the month and to do so\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5394,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/19\/dua-for-eid\/","url_meta":{"origin":27560,"position":3},"title":"Abu Umamah on Eid: Companions ask Allah to accept good deeds","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 19, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Muhammad ibn Ziyad reported: I was with Abu Umamah al-Bahili and others among the Companions of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him. When they would return from Eid prayer, they would say to each other, \u201cMay Allah accept good deeds from us and from you.\u201d Imam Ahmad said,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33326,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/31\/fasting-ashura-9th-muharram\/","url_meta":{"origin":27560,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on &#8216;Ashura: Fasting day of &#8216;Ashura with 9th of Muharram","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 31, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Hakam ibn al-A\u2019raj reported: I went to Ibn Abbas, may Allah be pleased with him, and I said, \u201cTell me about fasting the day of 'Ashura.\u201d Ibn Abbas said, \u201cWhen you see the crescent of the month of al-Muharram, count the days and wake up to fast on the ninth\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24850,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/05\/24\/salaf-fasting-remember-poor\/","url_meta":{"origin":27560,"position":5},"title":"Salaf on Fasting: Remember the poor, starving while fasting","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 24, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Hassan ibn Ahmad reported: He asked the commander of the faithful Al-Ma'mun 'Ali ibn Musa al-Rida, may Allah have mercy on him, \u201cIs there any benefit to fasting in the wisdom?\u201d Al-Ma'mun said, \u201cAllah Almighty knows what the impoverished endure of severe hunger, so He made the rich perform fasting\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/27560","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about"